  "explanation": "Two passes: left-to-right to find distance to nearest c on left, then right-to-left for right side. Take minimum.",
  "answer": "def shortestToChar(s, c):\n    n = len(s); res = [n] * n; pos = -n\n    for i in range(n):\n        if s[i] == c: pos = i\n        res[i] = i - pos\n    for i in range(n-1, -1, -1):\n        if s[i] == c: pos = i\n        res[i] = min(res[i], abs(i - pos))\n    return res",
